From the posters of Arizona in old-time western movies to the unique take on each of the side dishes, Bryan has done good.
Welcome to Cave Creek - we needed you.
The barbeque is all excellent, particularly the pulled pork and squash.
The sauce is tangy and the hot sauce has a memorable edge.
All the sides have a fun difference: the cole slaw with olives, the beans with a tasty sausage and the potato salad that provides a good balance with the barbeque.
The jalapeno pepper pickle is a fun surprise - sweet and just right.
For desert the mint chocolate chip ice cream sandwiches formed with chocolate chip cookies were an excellent finish.
Beer and wine is available, and you can eat outside to take in Black Mountain and Cave Creek.
Come on up to the high country and enjoy real western barbeque with a twist.
It's no Joe's Real BBQ, but it's awfully good and so much more convenient for those of us in the North Valley.

