Bryan's BBQ is tucked away in the cute little town of Cave Creek, luckily up the block from my daughter's new school.
It is so hard NOT to stop in for dinner everytime I pick her up.
Lately it has been a frequent go-to spot for the family when we are too tired to make dinner, or when we want to indulge in the best BBQ we've ever had.
The week wouldn't be complete without eating at Bryan's at least once.
AT LEAST.
I always get the pulled pork sandwich which has just the right amount of spice and flavor.
I always add a little spicy BBQ sauce for that extra kick.
The bun is slightly toasted and the edges have that little crunch, while the middle of the bun is soft from the moisture of the pulled pork.
Their fries are addicting, and served as a side in generous heaps with the perfect amount of salt.
Their cole slaw has sliced olives- both black and green- which give it a very pleasant and interesting twist.
I have yet to try their ribs, because when I find something I like, I stick to it.
But after reading some reviews on here I see that it's a must.
Oh, and you get a free soft drink if you wear a funny hat on Fridays.
Not that the place needs to offer this for me to keep coming back.
The BBQ is treat enough.

