BEST BBQ ON EARTH!
I have eaten at the most premier BBQ restaurants across the nation and Bryan out performs all of them.
This restaurant is simple perfection.
From the quality to the flavor, from the portions to the savory smell, from the prices to the decor, from the creativeness to the small town charm, from the friendly workers to the passionate trained chef, from the pulled pork to the whole chicken, from the homemade sides to the incredible hand-selected beer choices, from the minute you enter to the minute you leave...this is THE PERFECT EATING ESTABLISHMENT.
Because of Bryan's restaurant, I'm revamping my "rating" system for restaurants.
Instead of a 5 out of 5 (a rating which should be reserved for only Bryan's by the way), I'm developing a system from 1 to 25000.
Why 25000?
Well, that's the distance around the world.
My system is based on how many miles you would travel to eat at a particular restaurant.
I give this restaurant a 25000.
If I lived a mile away and the Great Wall of Cave Creek was built between me and Bryan's, I would fly around the world, in the opposite direction, 25000 miles, to eat here one time.
This place is not only my favorite restaurant in the world, but it's also the best food, regardless of price, I've ever eaten.
This quickly became my "last meal".
When they ask me what I want on my tombstone, when everyone else is saying, "Pepperoni and Cheese", I'll say, "Bryan's Pulled Pork with slaw on top and fries on the side please.
"   In summary, I give this place a 25000 out of 5.
If you go the rest of your life without eating here, you will regret it when you enter heaven and the big man is serving up Bryan's.
It should be on the top 10 places to see before you die.
Ok, I've embellished a little, but not by much.
Honestly, IT'S THAT GOOD!

