I thought, "This guy is from Texas.
" Nope, but his wife is.
The brisket was lean, smoky and perfectly done.
The smoke ring was evident but not as thick as you might see with longer pit time.
The ribs were great.
Very, very good.
Sauce was tasty and sides, potato salad and beans, up to par.
Overall, very good good.
The only downside I saw was the lack of a sausage choice.
But, he said he was looking at including it at a later date.

