I'm sorry, but however decent the food may be, I just can't frequent a barbecue restaurant that misspells the word 'barbecue' in its name.
"Barbeque" would be pronounced "barbeck.
"  Yes, I know that this misspelling has become so common that many dictionaries now allow it as an "alternate" spelling.
But it's still WRONG.
There is no word in ANY language in which the suffix "que" is pronounced "cue.
"    The next time you want to say 'what' to a Spanish speaker (que?
), say "cue?
" and see if he or she knows what you're talking about.

