I don't care for olives so I skip the slaw side and almost always go with the beans.
They tend to be just a tiny bit spicy with nice chunks of meat mixed in.
The pulled-pork is probably my favorite but I often get the pulled-chicken sandwich as well.
My only complaint about the chicken is easily remedied by adding BBQ sauce.
I think the chicken would be a little better if it came with a little more sauce on it or was a little juicer.
The pricing is a little higher than I would expect for a run-of-the-mill BBQ joint but, then again, it's not just a run-of-the-mill joint.
My wife and I try to get in there about once a week.

